                            <comment id="15753816" author="lefty@hortonworks.com" created="Fri, 16 Dec 2016 08:30:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Doc note:  This adds &lt;b&gt;hive.llap.daemon.headroom.memory.per.instance.mb&lt;/b&gt; to HiveConf.java and changes the default of &lt;b&gt;hive.llap.daemon.memory.per.instance.mb&lt;/b&gt; back to 4096 (after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-15159&quot; title=&quot;LLAP ContainerRunner should not reduce the available heap while distributing to individual executors&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-15159&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-15159&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; changed it to 3276, also in 2.2.0).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Only &lt;b&gt;hive.llap.daemon.headroom.memory.per.instance.mb&lt;/b&gt; needs to be documented in the wiki.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/Hive/Configuration+Properties#ConfigurationProperties-LLAP&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Configuration Properties &amp;#8211; LLAP &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Added a TODOC2.2 label.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Edit (22/Feb/17):  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-15959&quot; title=&quot;LLAP: fix headroom calculation and move it to daemon&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-15959&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-15959&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; removes &lt;b&gt;hive.llap.daemon.headroom.memory.per.instance.mb&lt;/b&gt; in 2.2.0, so it doesn&apos;t need to be documented after all.  Removing the TODOC2.2 label.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15796677" author="sseth" created="Wed, 4 Jan 2017 00:26:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hive --service llap takes the following 3 parameters before the patch &lt;br/&gt;
cache - the actual cache size&lt;br/&gt;
size - the cotnainer size&lt;br/&gt;
xmx - the xmx size for the process&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, checking the headroom within LlapDaemon doesn&apos;t really help - since the Xmx value has already been set. Executors may not use this - but JVM can grow to this size before GC actually kicks in.&lt;br/&gt;
These should be enough to control the headroom. I don&apos;t think we need another explicit config for the headroom. Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
